    "en": {
      "title": "July 2022 Sri Lanka's Export Performance",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to data released by Sri Lanka Customs, merchandise export earnings in July 2022 were recorded at US$ 1,128.7 million.",
        "It is a growth of 2.25% compared to the previous year, and this was mainly due to higher export earnings of garments and textiles, said the Export Development Board.",
        "The estimated value of services exports for the January-July 2022 period was $1,146 million, an increase of 5.39% over the corresponding period of 2021.",
        "Services exports estimated by the Export Development Board comprise of ICT/BPM, construction, financial services / transport and logistics services."
      ],
